Vibrational Analysis Tests

Methane. tests without molecular symmetry (POINT GROUP)
a) methan-opt-nosymm.inp
b) methan-in-nosymm.inp
c) methan-fd-nosymm.inp
d) methan-fd-sphere.inp (using only a spherical selection of atoms.
   does not make a lot of sense here, besides testing the feature)
e) methan-pt-nosymm.inp (using tuckerman/martyna instead of hockney) 
f) methan-lr-nosymm.inp (using tuckerman/martyna instead of hockney)
                        (SYMMETRY 0, experimental)

Methane. tests with molecular symmetry (POINT GROUP AUTO)
f) methan-opt.inp
g) methan-in.inp
h) methan-fd.inp
i) methan-pt.inp  (note. as of CPMD v3.9, not yet supported)
k) methan-lr.inp  (using tuckerman/martyna instead of hockney)

tests a) and b) as well as f) and g) have to be run in sequence.

last check: CPMD v3.9.2 (20041223-cvs), Axel Kohlmeyer 
methan-lr-nosymm.inp: failed, wavefuntion 'corrupt' after first perturbation
methan-opt.inp:       when running in parallel, first step takes excessively long.
methan-lr.inp:        broken, same symptoms as in nosymm case.

